<span id="freeTextContainer4167786947899834413">It&apos;s not that this isn&apos;t a well written, thought provoking book. It is both of those things. It just isn&apos;t the kind of book that I like to read, because it&apos;s just too...sad. Too painful. Too much for me, with my delicate sensibilities. <br/><br/>It is, in fact, quite a good book. If you like Richard Adams, or if you do not like animal testing and are looking to get emotionally charged up about it, this would be a good book to read. If you are extremely sensitive about unreasonable abuse/violence to animal</span>
  <span id="freeText4167786947899834413" style="display:none">It's not that this isn't a well written, thought provoking book. It is both of those things. It just isn't the kind of book that I like to read, because it's just too...sad. Too painful. Too much for me, with my delicate sensibilities. <br /><br />It is, in fact, quite a good book. If you like Richard Adams, or if you do not like animal testing and are looking to get emotionally charged up about it, this would be a good book to read. If you are extremely sensitive about unreasonable abuse/violence to animals, you probably should not read this book. <br /><br />I read it a couple of years ago, so that's all I've got, cause that's all I remember. I hope it helps.</span>
