<span id="freeTextContainer10211906705916077872">What started as a really good book suddenly became a chore to read. That doesn&apos;t mean I didn&apos;t enjoy it there were just several times in the story that felt unnecessarily long winded and not intrical to the plot. <br/>If you are a dog lover I would not recommend this book. The cruelty that our protagonists Sniter and Rowlf go through would make the puppy lovers of America call PETA on Richard Adams. It is the result of the experiments placed on them that make Sniter have random turns about the place </span>
  <span id="freeText10211906705916077872" style="display:none">What started as a really good book suddenly became a chore to read. That doesn't mean I didn't enjoy it there were just several times in the story that felt unnecessarily long winded and not intrical to the plot. <br />If you are a dog lover I would not recommend this book. The cruelty that our protagonists Sniter and Rowlf go through would make the puppy lovers of America call PETA on Richard Adams. It is the result of the experiments placed on them that make Sniter have random turns about the place "It's the flies their in my head again Rowlf". These spastic turns put into motion a lot of the conflicts the two dogs encounter as the "white coats" hunt them down.<br />This book has been called Watership Down for dogs (mostly because they're both written by the same author) but what makes them different is that Plague Dogs delves more into the psychological elements of survival where as Watership was a fight or flight thriller. Plague Dogs is good counterpart to it's more famous predecessor it will come down to reader's preference on which book is better.</span>
